race.comment: FLAMING EYES (6) is the only horse in this race coming back in distance after a couple of placings over 2200m. She is rock hard fit, Holder sticks, and she draws the inside, all of which are in her favour. She looks a key winning chance again. ON THE MAP (9) keeps racing well without the best of luck. She did a bit of work but there was still merit in her run at 1600m last time. She can win. PALACE INVITE (3) is the one stepping up to 1600m for the first time that might be able to improve sharply. His form isn't flattering but he is bred to relish the mile and he's drawn well. ROYAL MUSE (10) and INDIAMO (1) appeal for wider plays in a modest maiden to start the program.
